How to use tasks_upsert correctly:
- ADD work: list items in `new_subtasks` (exact text; content_id is derived from the text).
- CHANGE progress: list `{content_id, status}` in `subtask_updates`, using a content_id shown in the ledger below (lattice: pending → in_progress → done|cancelled, never backwards).
- RENAME a subtask: add a NEW subtask with the new text AND cancel the old one (you cannot edit text in place — content_id is the text hash).
- DROP a subtask no longer needed: set it `cancelled`.

What is NOT allowed: a tasks_upsert with neither a new_subtask nor a subtask_update.

